summary:
**Stabilization and Peace Consolidation**

* Support Congolese authorities to strengthen and reform security and judicial institutions (l)
* Assist in strengthening FARDC military capacity, including military justice and police (m)
* Support police reform, including training and equipment for Congolese National Police (PNC) (n)
* Develop and implement a multi-year joint UN justice support programme (o)
* Support efforts to consolidate State authority and develop rule of law institutions (p)

**Elections, Resources, and Demining**

* Provide technical and logistical support for national and local elections (q)
* Support Government efforts to prevent illicit trade in natural resources and support pilot project to improve mineral product traceability (r)
* Assist Government in enhancing demining capacity (s)

**Monitoring and Implementation**

* Monitor implementation of measures imposed by resolution 1896 (2009) (t)
The Security Council:

7. Authorizes MONUSCO to seize or collect arms and related materiel whose presence in the Democratic Republic of the Congo violates resolution 1896 (2009) and dispose of them, and assist Congolese customs authorities in implementing resolution 1896 (2009);

13. Urges international community and donors to support MONUSCO's DDRRR activities and calls on the Government of the Democratic Republic of the Congo and neighboring States to remain engaged;

14. Calls on the Government of the Democratic Republic of the Congo to cooperate with the Special Representatives of the Secretary-General on Children and Armed Conflicts and on Sexual Violence in Conflict;

15. Requests the Secretary-General to ensure MONUSCO's compliance with the UN's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;

16. Encourages MONUSCO to interact with the civilian population to raise awareness about its mandate and activities;

17. Calls on MONUSCO to collect information on threats against civilians and human rights abuses and bring them to the attention of authorities;

18. Demands that armed groups, particularly FDLR and LRA, cease violence and human rights abuses against civilians;

19. Commends troop- and police-contributing countries and donors to MONUC and calls on Member States to provide required force enablers;

20. Requests the Secretary-General to report on progress by 11 October 2010, 21 January 2011, and 13 May 2011;

21. Demands that parties cooperate with MONUSCO and ensure security and access for UN personnel;
